reviews.snippet:
Absolutely delicious. I had both the falafel and the lamb sandwich. The falafel was incredibly crispy on the outside and soft on the inside. Honestly even better than the ones I had back in Egypt. The lamb sandwich was packed with flavor and perfectly seasoned, wrapped in fresh bread that held everything together nicely.

Portions were generous and I left feeling full and satisfied. The staff were friendly and the atmosphere was relaxed. I will definitely be coming back to sit down and enjoy the experience more next time. Highly recommended if you’re craving authentic Middle Eastern flavor done right.

お気に入りのイスラエル料理屋さんが閉店してしまい、悲しみに暮れながら見つけたAbuEssamさん。ファラフェルプレートとチキンコシャリをシェアーして頂きました。シンプルかつ繊細なお味、とても満足でした。神楽坂駅からすぐ、ゆっくり出来る雰囲気ではありませんが
切れることなくお客様がいらっしゃっていました。
デザートのテイクアウトの方が多くいたので次は頂いてみたいです。

お気に入りのイスラエル料理屋さんが閉店してしまい、悲しみに暮れながら見つけたAbuEssamさん。ファラフェルプレートとチキンコシャリをシェアーして頂きました。シンプルかつ繊細なお味、とても満足でした。神楽坂駅からすぐ、ゆっくり出来る雰囲気ではありませんが

extracted_snippet.translated: I was saddened when my favorite Israeli restaurant closed down, but then I found AbuEssam. We shared a falafel plate and chicken koshari. The simple yet delicate flavors were very satisfying. It's right next to Kagurazaka Station, and while it's not a relaxing atmosphere, there were always customers coming in. Many people were ordering takeaway desserts, so I'd like to try that next time.
